Want to stay warm but also protect from colds this winter period? Lentil soup is a perfect dish that you can prepare for yourself and your loved ones. Lentils are rich in fibre, folate, and potassium making them a great choice for the heart, and managing blood pressure and cholesterol. The dish is vegan and extremely cheap to make. The soup is infused with ginger, lemon, cinnamon, and turmeric, all brilliant agents for combatting colds. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Using a sufuria, warm the oil before adding the onions. Cook for 5 minutes or until they turn light brown. Step 2 Add your spices and stir to bring out the flavours. Add in the blended tomatoes, water and lentils then stir. Reduce the heat and cover. Let it simmer for 30 minutes, and bring to boil. Step 3 Stir occasionally then add the tomato paste before adding flour and a little water. Serve with fresh lemon juice, chopped Dhania, and toasted bread.